-- VeriFone quarterly loss narrows
-- 
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 04:14PM EDT
-- None



June 5 (Reuters) - VeriFone Systems Inc <PAY.N>, a maker of credit card swipe machines, reported a 9 percent rise in revenue for the second quarter as customers upgrade their equipment to accept the new credit cards embedded with chips.

Net loss attributable to the company narrowed to $23.9  million, or 22 cents per share, in the quarter ended April 30, from $58.4 million, or 54 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw1TmXJHa]